original: Lundström, Stig Harald Ingemar, stads fisk al-, stadsfogde, Falkenberg, f. 25/7/02 i Upps. av folksk :insp. K. V. L. o. Elna Jönsson. G. 39 m. Annie Pettersison. Barn: Elna Britta f. 40, S,tig-Björn 42. — Jur. kand. 42. För-ordn. s. stads fisk al, polismäst. i Västerås, Jönköp., Örebro, Karlstad 36-39, stadsfiskal i Avesta 40-42, stadsfiskal-stadstogde i Falkenb. fr. 42. Ordf. i tax:nd sed. 43.
translated: Lundström, Stig Harald Ingemar, city fisherman, city bailiff, Falkenberg, born on July 25th, 1902 in Uppsala. Son of elementary school inspector K. V. L. and Elna Jönsson. Married in 1939 to Annie Pettersson. Children: Elna Britta, born in 1940, and Stig-Björn, born in 1942. Graduated with a degree in law in 1942. Appointed as city fisherman, chief of police in Västerås, Jönköping, Örebro, and Karlstad from 1936 to 1939, city fisherman in Avesta from 1940 to 1942, and city fisherman-city bailiff in Falkenberg from 1942 onwards. Chairman of the tax committee since 1943.
